<h2>ChainLink 0.3.454</h2>
<p class="sub">A big update — everything since 0.3.438.</p>
<ul>
  <li><b>New manual chapter: "Which rider are you?"</b> — 17 short rider profiles
  (racer, randonneur, tourer, commuter, indoor rider, returning from a break…)
  that point you at the parts of the app built for you. Start there if the manual
  feels long.</li>
  <li><b>AI Coach settings, redesigned</b> — one clear pick-one list of engines,
  privacy options on top, and a model picker for each cloud engine (use exactly
  the model you want).</li>
  <li><b>Settings page design pass</b> — simpler layout, less clutter, details
  tucked into expanding sections; Import and Preferences are now separate cards.</li>
  <li><b>Events</b> — FKT attempts with target times and an attempts log;
  multi-day events with daily distance/time targets that shape your training
  plan; brevet records with Audax/Super&nbsp;Randonneur progress built from your
  real rides.</li>
  <li><b>Bring your coach's plan</b> — Training → Import a plan: paste it, review
  what was read, adopt it. ChainLink tracks compliance without rewriting your
  coach's structure.</li>
  <li><b>Bikes</b> — mark a bike out of commission, away in another location, or
  borrowed/rented; ride assignment and totals respect it.</li>
  <li><b>Aspirations</b> — write a goal in your own words on the Goals page
  ("I want to get faster at club crits") and the coach tracks it against your
  actual numbers.</li>
  <li><b>Week start</b> — choose Monday or Sunday weeks (Settings → Preferences);
  all weekly stats follow.</li>
  <li><b>Weather day call</b> — on a genuinely unrideable day the Overview
  weather card now suggests what to do instead: your cross-training sports, the
  trainer, or an earned day off, backed by your training data.</li>
  <li>Plus: Rides refresh automatically after a Sync, faster page loads, and
  assorted fixes.</li>
</ul>
]]></description>
